Description:
Ballistics of the 122x785mmR OF-471 HE-Frag projectile, fired with the Zh-471 charge, from the 122mm corps gun M1931/37. The ammunition was produced in the PRC as the WB013P.

The ballistics is identical to and originated with the 122mm M1931 (A-19) gun. The M1931/37 mates the tube of the M1931 gun with the chasis of the 152 mm gun-howitzer M1937 (ML-20). Also adapted as the main armament 122mm self-propelled gun mod. 1931/44 (ISU-122).

Breech to start of rifling measures 8.81 dm, (loaded) chamber measures 7.03 dm in length and 9.898 L in volume. Barrel measures 5650 mm. Zh-471 charge loads 6.82 kg of 22/1 tubular grains. Develops 800 m/s with a peak breech (copper crusher gauge) pressure of 2750 kgf/cm^2.
